== Events == * [[Emperor Seinei]] 1st year（[[Julian calendar]] [[480]] [[February 11]]） – The 22nd Emperor, [[Seinei]], ascends to the throne. * [[Empress Kōgyoku]] 1st year（[[Julian calendar]] [[642]] [[February 19]]） – Princess Takara, consort of [[Emperor Jomei]], ascends as the 35th monarch, [[Empress Kōgyoku]]. * {{ill|An'ei|ja|安永}} 7th year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[1778]] [[February 18]]） – [[Tanuma Okitsugu]] appointed as {{ill|Rōjū|ja|老中}}. * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久}} 2nd year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[1862]] [[February 13]]） – [[Sakashita Gate Incident]]: {{ill|Andō Nobumasa|ja|安藤信正}}, a key figure in Princess [[Kazunomiya]]’s marriage, is attacked by Mito Domain samurai. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 1st year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[1868]] [[February 8]]） – The [[Meiji government]] formally announces the [[Restoration of Imperial Rule]] to foreign embassies.
== Births == * {{ill|An'ei|ja|安永}} 7th year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[1778]] [[February 11]]） – {{ill|帆足万里|ja|帆足万里}}, Confucian scholar and reformist (d. [[1852]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保}} 15th year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[1844]] [[March 3]]） – {{ill|Aoki Shūzō|ja|青木周蔵}}, diplomat and politician (d. [[1914]]). * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政}} 5th year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[1858]] [[February 28]]） – {{ill|Motoda Hajime|ja|元田肇}}, politician, Speaker of the House of Representatives (d. [[1938]]). * [[Meiji]] 5th year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[1872]] [[February 23]]） – {{ill|Hirakushi Denchū|ja|平櫛田中}}, sculptor (d. [[1979]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Ninpei|ja|仁平}} 3rd year（[[Julian calendar]] [[1153]] [[February 10]]） – {{ill|Taira no Tadamori|ja|平忠盛}}, military leader, father of [[Taira no Kiyomori]] (b. [[1096]]). * {{ill|Ōei|ja|応永}} 24th year（[[Julian calendar]] [[1417]] [[February 1]]） – {{ill|Reizei Tametoshi|ja|冷泉為尹}}, waka poet (b. [[1361]]).
== Commemorations == * {{ill|Koshōgatsu|ja|小正月}} (Minor New Year) * {{ill|Jōgen (festival)|ja|上元}} (First Full Moon Festival)
== Fictional Events == === Fictional Births === * {{ill|Jōgan|ja|貞観}} 18th year（[[Julian calendar]] [[876]] [[February 13]]） – {{nihongo|Ōya no Yotsugi|大宅世継}}, fictional chronicler from *[[Ōkagami]]*.<ref>『大鏡』「序」より。</ref>
